# Critical: prevents COPY in any Dockerfile from baking secrets / build
# artifacts / VCS metadata into image layers (which are also published
# to GitHub Actions cache when builds use `cache-to: type=gha`).
#
# The Dockerfile.prod multi-stage build only needs source + Cargo
# manifests; tests, .env files, build artifacts, and editor state are
# never required by the build.

# ─── Secrets and env files ─────────────────────────────────────────
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/tests/.env*
*.pem
*.key
*_key
*_secret*
*_token*
**/credentials.json
**/.aws

# ─── VCS + workspace metadata ──────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github
.hg
.svn

# ─── Build artifacts (huge + unneeded) ─────────────────────────────
**/target
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/build
**/.next
**/.nuxt
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/*.pyc
**/*.swp

# ─── Local caches (rootfs alone is ~800 MB) ────────────────────────
.ziee-cache
.cargo

# ─── Editor state ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea
.vscode
.fleet
*.iml
.DS_Store

# ─── Test fixtures + binary artifacts that aren't shipped ──────────
**/sandbox-rootfs/.stage-*
mcpserver*
rcpa-mcpserver*

# ─── Documentation only used by humans, not the build ──────────────
**/*.md
!**/README.md
# Built-in skills are baked into the server binary via include_dir! at compile
# time (server/src/modules/skill/builtin.rs) and each is a lone SKILL.md — they
# MUST survive the *.md exclusion above or the image ships with zero skills.
!**/resources/builtin-skills/**
.claude
.plans
.sec-audits
